<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="345" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0090/138e: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-20">May 20, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1298. American interests—Japan. Department’s 1234, May 13, paragraph
                                2. Japanese Government should be informed that charter for <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> has been signed and it is expected
                                that vessel will leave New York June 9 and arrive Lourenço Marques
                                July 6 calling at Rio de Janeiro.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>